<!doctype html>

<html>
<head>
    <title>Epulo</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css">
    <link href="/css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/css/bootstrap-social.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <!--<link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>-->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <link href="/css/main.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- HTML5 Shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/html5shiv/3.7.0/html5shiv.js"></script>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/respond.js/1.3.0/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
</head>
<body>
<div id="fb-root"></div>
<script>(function(d, s, id) {
  var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];
  if (d.getElementById(id)) return;
  js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;
  js.src = "//connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1&appId={{app_id}}";
  fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);
}(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));</script>

<div class="container">
  <h1>Welcome to Epulo!</h1>
  <div class="login">
    <a href="/auth/facebook" class="btn btn-block btn-social btn-facebook">
      <i class="fa fa-facebook"></i> Sign in with Facebook
    </a>
  </div>
  <div class="fb-facepile" data-app-id="{{app_id}}" data-max-rows="1" data-colorscheme="light" data-size="medium" data-show-count="true"></div>
  <hr>

  <div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Request and Offer Ingredients</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <p>Epulo connects you to other people cooking in your community so you can exchange ingredients from your household kitchens. It's easy and fun.
        <li>Have extra bananas? Create a bulletin offering bananas to your neighbors.</li> 
        <li>Need vanilla extract? Request it from someone who has it in their inventory.</li>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Foster Community</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <p>All the exchanges on Epulo are <strong>hyper-local</strong>: these are people you can walk to in a few minutes. Exchanges involve no money and are driven by the helpfulness of the community.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Reduce Waste</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <p>No more throwing out ingredients that are perfectly usable. Create a bulletin so that others can use your items and combat squandered resources.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script src="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>